OL,6,FAviation consultant John Strickland
OL,7,Fsaid that "turbulence happens", but
OL,8,Fwith millions of flights operated each
OL,9,Fyear, incidents are "limited" and
OL,10,F"fatalities are rare".
OL,12,FHe said: "Exposure is greater in
OL,13,Fdifferent parts of the world.
OL,15,F"The South Atlantic, Africa and the
OL,16,FBay of Bengal are all places that
OL,17,Fspring to mind where there's a greater
OL,18,Fincidence.
